## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Framework and Architecture
  - React 18+ with TypeScript
  - Component-driven architecture with a clear separation of concerns
  - Use React Query or SWR for data fetching with safe data handling and caching
  - Centralized state management for dashboards (e.g., Zustand or Redux Toolkit) with selectors
- UI Components
  - Reusable Card, Button, Input, Select, Toggle, Badge, Tooltip, Modal, ChartCard, and List components
  - Cards must implement hover/focus states per design guidelines
  - Tables or dense lists with accessible semantics (aria-labels, proper headers)
- Accessibility
  - Keyboard navigable, screen-reader friendly, high contrast modes
  - Focus ring visibility and descriptive aria attributes
- Data Handling and Safety
  - All arrays treated as data ?? [] before mapping, filtering, reducing
  - Array.isArray checks when operating on dynamic API results
  - Initialize all array states with useState<Type[]>([])
  - Validate API shapes: ensure data is an array: const items = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - Optional chaining for nested objects: obj?.prop?.nested
  - Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}
- Routing and Pages
  - FinanceDashboard page as root with sub-sections as tabs or cards
  - Subscriptions & Billing page
  - Transactions & Categorization page
- Performance and Security
  - Debounced search, pagination, and virtualization for long lists
  - Client-side input validation and error boundaries
  - Ensure sensitive data is not logged; implement proper error handling

### Backend
- API Design
  - Endpoints to fetch categorized transactions, subscription data, anomalies, forecasts, monthly close tasks, and agent recommendations
  - Endpoints to ingest transactions, categorize, and apply rules
  - Endpoints to connect billing processors and manage subscriptions
  - Endpoints to retrieve and mutate monthly close checklists and approvals
  - Endpoints to fetch cronjob runs, permissions, and run artifacts
- Data Models (Database)
  - Transactions: id, date, amount, currency, category_id, status, notes, user_id, merchant, metadata
  - Categories: id, name, parent_id, color
  - Subscriptions: id, user_id, provider, plan, amount, currency, next_billing_date, status, churn_risk_score, is_tracked
  - Anomalies: id, transaction_id, detected_by, severity, rationale, status
  - Forecasts: id, horizon, series, value, confidence
  - MonthlyCloseTasks: id, name, due_date, owner_id, status, related_runs
  - AgentRecommendations: id, context, action, expected_roi, confidence
  - CronJobs: id, name, schedule, timezone, target, input_payload, permissions, constraints, safety_rails, retry_policy, outputs
- Business Logic
  - Validation of inputs, idempotent operations, audit trails for all mutating actions
  - Real-time or near-real-time anomaly detection triggers
  - Categorization rules engine with allow-list/deny-list and user-configurable mappings
  - Forecasting engine integration (historical data, seasonality, scenario modeling)
  - Monthly close workflow orchestration with approvals
- Security
  - Authentication (JWT/OAuth as per project standards)
  - Authorization roles: admin, finance_agent, analyst, user
  - Input validation and server-side guards
  - Rate limiting and auditing

### Integration
- Data Flow
  - FinanceAutomationBridge connects ingestion, categorization, anomalies, forecasting, and monthly close to the frontend via API endpoints
  - Transactions feed is categorized and enriched with rules; anomalies feed triggers alerts
  - Subscriptions data is enriched with churn risk and spend limit checks; billing processors connected
  - Forecasts feed to the UI with scenario controls
  - Monthly close tasks and approvals flow back to the dashboard
- Event Handling
  - WebSocket/Push or polling for anomaly alerts and run status updates
  - Audit trail hooks on every mutating action
- Data Consistency
  - Use idempotent operations for updates
  - Validate shapes and ensure arrays default to [] using data ?? [] across responses
- Error Handling
  - Centralized error boundaries; user-friendly error messages and retry strategies

---

## User Experience Flow
1. User lands on Finance Dashboard
   - Sees SnapshotTiles with Balance, Monthly Spend, Forecast, and Savings Opportunities
   - Views a dense TransactionsOverview with categorized transactions; uses search and filters
   - Checks AnomaliesPanel for recent flags
   - Examines ForecastingPanel for scenario comparisons
   - Opens MonthlyClosePanel to review reconciliations and pending approvals
   - Embraces AgentRecommendationsPanel for optimization suggestions
2. User navigates to Subscriptions & Billing
   - Manages subscriptions (own and tracked), checks churn risk, sets spend limits, and connects billing processors
3. User engages Transactions & Categorization
   - Creates/cuts rules, manually categorizes transactions, marks exceptions
   - Rules engine applies in real time to new transactions
4. User interacts with agent-driven actions
   - AgentRecommendations present actionable steps; user accepts/rejects with rationale captured
   - Approvals queue handles any scheduled actions requiring human review
5. All actions generate run artifacts
   - Audit trails, logs, diffs, and inter-agent traces stored and accessible

---

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: [Schema details]
- Transaction
  - id: string
  - date: string (ISO)
  - amount: number
  - currency: string
  - categoryId: string | null
  - status: 'pending'|'posted'|'flagged'
  - notes: string
  - userId: string
  - merchant: string
  - metadata: object
- Category
  - id: string
  - name: string
  - parentId: string | null
  - color: string
- Subscription
  - id: string
  - userId: string
  - provider: string
  - plan: string
  - amount: number
  - currency: string
  - nextBillingDate: string
  - status: 'active'|'paused'|'canceled'
  - churnRiskScore: number
  - isTracked: boolean
- Anomaly
  - id: string
  - transactionId: string
  - detectedBy: string
  - severity: 'low'|'medium'|'high'
  - rationale: string
  - status: 'open'|'closed'
- Forecast
  - id: string
  - horizon: string
  - series: string
  - value: number
  - confidence: number
- MonthlyCloseTask
  - id: string
  - name: string
  - dueDate: string
  - ownerId: string
  - status: 'open'|'in_progress'|'done'
  - relatedRuns: string[]
- AgentRecommendation
  - id: string
  - context: string
  - action: string
  - expectedROI: number
  - confidence: number
- CronJob
  - id: string
  - name: string
  - schedule: string
  - timezone: string
  - target: string
  - inputPayload: object
  - permissions: string
  - constraints: object
  - safetyRails: object
  - retryPolicy: object
  - outputs: object

API Endpoints: [Routes and methods]
- GET /api/finance/dashboard (GET)
  - returns: { balances, spend, forecast, opportunities, transactions: Transaction[], subscriptions: Subscription[], anomalies: Anomaly[], forecastData: Forecast[], monthlyCloseItems: MonthlyCloseTask[], recommendations: AgentRecommendation[] }
  - safety guards: data ?? [], Array.isArray checks
- POST /api/finance/ingest-transactions (POST)
  - body: { transactions: Transaction[] }
- POST /api/finance/categorize (POST)
  - body: { ruleId: string, transactionIds: string[] }
- GET /api/finance/subscriptions (GET)
  - returns: Subscription[]
- POST /api/finance/subscriptions/connect (POST)
  - body: { provider: string, credentials: any }
- GET /api/finance/anomalies (GET)
  - returns: Anomaly[]
- GET /api/finance/forecast (GET)
  - returns: Forecast[]
- GET /api/finance/monthly-close (GET)
  - returns: MonthlyCloseTask[]
- POST /api/finance/close/approve (POST)
  - body: { taskId: string, approverId: string, notes?: string }
- GET /api/finance/recommendations (GET)
  - returns: AgentRecommendation[]
- GET /api/cronjobs (GET)
  - returns: CronJob[]
- POST /api/cronjobs/run (POST)
  - body: { cronJobId: string }

Security: 
- JWT-based authentication; roles: admin, finance_agent, analyst, user
- Endpoint authorization checks
- Data minimization; sensitive data masked where not required

Validation:
- All inputs validated server-side
- Use safe defaults on responses: const items = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- Use data ?? [] for Supabase-like results
- Optional chaining and destructuring with defaults everywhere

---

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] The Finance Dashboard renders without runtime errors, and all array operations guard against null/undefined by using (data ?? []) or Array.isArray checks
- [ ] All frontend states initialize as arrays where appropriate: useState<Type[]>([]) for lists and collections
- [ ] API responses are validated to always return arrays or empty arrays; no undefined array results propagate to UI
- [ ] Transactions can be categorized manually, and categorization rules are created/edited with immediate effect on the feed
- [ ] Subscriptions can be added, edited, and connected to billing processors; churn risk and spend limits appear and update correctly
- [ ] Anomalies panel shows flagged transactions with agent rationale and remediation steps
- [ ] Forecasting charts render correctly with multiple scenarios and accurate data binding
- [ ] Monthly close checklist items reflect status changes and can be approved; audit trail is accessible
- [ ] Agent recommendations are presented with confidence scores and option to execute or dismiss with rationale
- [ ] All sensitive actions require appropriate approvals or constraints as configured by permissions

---

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project’s design system and ensure consistency across pages. The UI should be dense but legible, with clear hierarchy and accessible interactions. All components must visually align with the specified color palette, typography, spacing, and card treatments. Implement micro-interactions for hover, focus, and actions that feel tactile but restrained.

---

## Visual Style

Color Palette:
- Primary background: #0B0B0C
- Secondary surface: #151718
- Tertiary surface / panel outline: #1F1F20
- Primary text / headings: #FFFFFF
- Secondary text / meta: #9DA3A6
- Subtle text / disabled: #56595B
- Accent (action / alert): #FF3B30
- Neutral highlight / icon fill: #CFCFCF
- Soft highlight / gloss: #E6E7E8
- Charts/Status accents: teal #00C2A8, amber #FFB020, purple #8B5CF6
- Dividers: rgba(255,255,255,0.03)
- Gradients: subtle gradient from #111213 to #1A1A1B inside cards

Typography & Layout:
- Font: Inter or similar geometric sans
- Headings: 20–28px, weight 600–700
- Card titles: 14–16px, weight 500–600
- Body: 12–14px, weight 400
- Microcopy: 11–12px, weight 300–400
- Spacing: 8px baseline grid; gutters 220–260px for sidebar
- Card padding: 16–20px; rounded corners 8–12px
- Layout alignment: left-aligned lists; dense card grids; consistent vertical rhythm

Key Design Elements
- Card Design: dark elevated cards, subtle borders, gentle shadows, hover lifts
- Navigation: left vertical sidebar with active pill indicator in accent color
- Data Visualization: minimal charts with low-contrast axes, colored series using the accent palette
- Interactive Elements: primary/secondary buttons, guarded inputs, toggles, chips, badges
- Micro-interactions: 120–200ms transitions, subtle elevations
- Badges: counts with neutral or accent colors

Design Philosophy
- Modern, minimal, developer-focused; dense information with clarity
- Emphasis on traceability, auditability, and control
- Consistent visual language across dashboard, lists, and charts
- UX goals: fast scanning, reliable automation with human-in-the-loop controls

---

### Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety (Non-Negotiable)
- Supabase-like results: use nullish coalescing for arrays: const items = data ?? []
- Array methods: guard all calls
  - (items ?? []).map(...)
  - Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
- React useState defaults for arrays: useState<Type[]>([])
- API response shapes: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- Optional chaining: safe access with ?. for nested API responses
- Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

---

### PROJECT CONTEXT CONNECTION
TARGET PAGE: Finance Dashboard
- Finance hub: categorized transactions, subscription management, anomalies, forecasting, monthly close checklist, agent recommendations
- Connected to Finance Automation: ingestion, categorization, anomaly detection, forecasting, monthly close workflows
- Subscriptions & Billing page: manage user-owned/tracked subscriptions, churn detection, spend limits, connect billing processors
- Transactions & Categorization page: list/manage transactions; manual categorization; categorization rules; mark exceptions

