=== TASK ===
# Finance Dashboard Prompt

Create a comprehensive, production-ready implementation plan for building the Finance Dashboard in the LifeOps platform. This task encompasses a central Finance hub with categorized transactions, subscription management, anomalies, forecasting, monthly close checklist, and agent recommendations for optimizing spend, plus two connected pages: Subscriptions & Billing and Transactions & Categorization. All code and architecture must be resilient to null/undefined data and guarded against common runtime errors as specified in the project’s mandatory coding standards.

---

## Overview
You will develop a modular, scalable Finance Dashboard composed of a central Finance Hub page and two connected pages (Subscriptions & Billing and Transactions & Categorization). The system integrates with Finance Automation workflows (ingestion, categorization, anomaly detection, forecasting, and monthly close), and supports agent-driven spend optimization recommendations. The UI should be dense, dark-themed, enterprise-grade, highly navigable for power users, and adhere to the provided design system and runtime safety rules.

---

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Finance Dashboard is the Finance hub for LifeOps, delivering a consolidated view into categorized transactions, active and tracked subscriptions, anomaly alerts, forecasting, and monthly close readiness. It also surfaces agent recommendations to optimize spend and allocate resources efficiently.

Goals:
- Provide a single command center for financial operations, with fast access to:
  - Categorized transactions: search, filter, bulk actions, and rule-based auto-categorization
  - Subscriptions management: user-owned and tracked subscriptions, churn risk indicators, spend limits, and billing processor integrations
  - Anomaly detection: real-time flags with agent rationale and remediation actions
  - Forecasting: revenue/expense forecast visuals with scenario toggles
  - Monthly close checklist: reconciliations, approvals, and audit trails
  - Agent recommendations: explainable, traceable actions for optimizing spend
- Ensure cohesive navigation with Subscriptions & Billing and Transactions & Categorization as connected pages. All interactions are captured with an audit trail and reversible where appropriate.

UI elements and visual guidance:
- Snapshot Tiles: at-a-glance balances, monthly spend, forecast, and savings opportunities
- Transaction Feed: categorized lines, live search, tagging, and rule-based auto-categorization hints
- Subscriptions Panel: recurring payments, churn risk indicators, spend-limit warnings, and processor connections
- Anomaly Alerts: flags with agent-provided rationale and recommended actions
- Monthly Close Checklist: items with status indicators, owner, due dates, and approvals
- Agent Recommendations: contextual prompts with confidence scores and potential ROI impact
- Global chrome: consistent dark UI with the specified color palette, typography, and spacing. Ensure responsive layout that preserves information density on large screens and scales gracefully to smaller viewports.

Connected APIs and data flows:
- Finance Automation services: ingestion, categorization, anomaly detection, forecasting, and monthly close orchestration
- Subscriptions service: manage user-owned and tracked subscriptions, churn analytics, spend limit enforcement, and billing processor integrations
- Transactions service: provide categorized transactions and rules engine
- Agents orchestrator: deliver explainable recommendations and run artifacts
- All API responses must be validated and guarded against null/undefined values (see runtime safety rules)

